Case called at 1:21 pm
Defendant Rene Aguilar Ramirez in custody, via video from the Jefferson County Jail with Attorney Elizabeth Svehlek from the Jefferson County Public Defenders Office. DA Susan V. Happ appeared for the State of Wisconsin.

Shawna Stevenoski sworn in as spanish interpreter.
Court verifies with Defendant that the DOB and address listed on the criminal complaint are correct.
Service of Complaint admitted; reading waived; charges and maximum penalties recited
Court has reviewed the criminal complaint and finds that it states probable cause to support Count #1.
Attorney Svehlek informs the Court that she was not able to conduct a financial evaluation, so currently is appearing for bond purposes only.
Court finds the video connection to be sight and sound sufficient. 
Bail/Bond recommendations presented by counsel.

Court requires $1,500.00 signature bond, with conditions: 
-No acts or threats of violence 
-Not to physically discipline any child
-No possession or consumption of any alcohol 
-No contact with JPM (DOB: 4/27/07) or Candelaria Perez
-No presence at 1023 W. Main St Apt. 8A Watertown; except shall be allowed presence on one occasion to obtain personal belongings if it is done upon reasonable notice and conditioned upon supervision by a law enforcement officer.

Preliminary Hearing time limits waived by both parties.
Right to counsel given; constructive waiver of counsel warnings given

Court allows the Defendant 48 hours to provide a new mailing address to the Clerk of Courts.
